item.title: Fluke or Fate? Embracing Uncertainty to Live a Fuller Life with Brian Klaas
item.description: In this episode, Brian Klaas explains the concept of whether things are a fluke or fate, and explores how embracing uncertainty can lead to a living a fuller life. Brian makes the case that randomness and chaos might be exactly what makes our lives matter so much, and how we tend to worship at the “Altar of Progress in the Church of Control.” We make plans, set goals, and these are good things, but we only have so much control... item.title: Episode 326: Picture Day
item.description: It’s new story time this week! Charissa kicks things off with a one about baking in the sun before a trip to the DMV which sure enough turns into a frantic rummaging session thru the car to find things to put on her face. Next up, the ladies reminisce about school picture day, and here is where the fun really begins; with Erin telling the story of how her sister thought she had died after a surgery to have her ears pulled back...
